Q: If a student asks a teacher an honest question and gets an honest reply, but the student doesn&#8217;t believe the teacher, what recourse does the teacher have?
<br>A: It doesn&#8217;t harm the teacher.
<br>Q: Isn&#8217;t that selfish?
<br>A: How? Should he cry because the student didn&#8217;t believe? <span class=date>11/16/80</span>
